import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(['Speed Distribution'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='dir', y='speed', hue='dirCat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between direction and speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Speed')
    plt.legend(title='Direction Category')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.countplot(x='dirCat', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of direction categories?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Direction Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Direction Categories', loc='upper right', labels=data['dirCat'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='dir_rad', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['dir_rad'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['dir_rad'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of direction in radians?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Direction in Radians")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
